def: Negligence or fault, as distinguishable from dolus (deceit,fraud), which implies intent, culpa being imputable to defect ofintellect, dolus to defect of heart. Wharton.
Disagreeing; contrary; differing; -- opposed to consentaneous.[R.] Barrow.
A coral island or islands, consisting of a belt of coral reef,partly submerged, surrounding a central lagoon or depression; alagoon island.
A contrivance to fasten logs together in rafting; -- used bylumbermen. [U.S.]

Any one of numerous species of scaraboid beetles belonging toScarabæus, Copris, Phanæus, and allied genera. The female lays hereggs in a globular mass of dung which she rolls by means of her hindlegs to a burrow excavated in the earth in which she buries it.
To cause to coagulate or thicken; to cause to congeal; tocurdle.Does it curd thy blood To say I am thy mother Shak.

Tending to draw the attention or affections; attractive; as,engaging manners or address.-- En*ga"ging*ly, adv.-- En*ga"ging*ness, n. Engaging and disengaging gear or machinery,that in which, or by means of which, one part is alternately broughtinto gear or out of gear with another part, as occasion may require.
Having the ratio of one to seven. Bp. Wilkins.
To face or look (one) out of countenance; to resist or beardown by bold looks or effrontery; to brave. Shak.Having outfaced all the world. South.
The outer layer of the blastoderm; the ectoderm. SeeBlastoderm, Delamination.
